# Force Windows shell scripts to be checked out with CRLF line endings.
# Without this, cross-platform git (or contributor configs without autocrlf)
# can land .bat files with LF endings, which cmd.exe parses incorrectly ???
# fragments like 'EM' (from REM with stripped 'R') get executed as commands.
# See scripts\dev_register.bat for the original reproducer.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
